A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 2 of Article 5 of Chapter 2 of Title 14 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to venue relative to business corporations, so as to provide that certain
3 domestic corporations maintaining a principal place of business in Georgia shall be deemed
4 to reside and to be subject to venue in the county in Georgia where the defendant maintains
5 such principal place of business; to provide for determinations regarding the principal place
6 of business for certain domestic corporations; to provide for statutory construction; to
7 provide for related matters; to provide for an effective date and applicability; to repeal
8 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
10 SECTION 1.
11 Part 2 of Article 5 of Chapter 2 of Title 14 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
12 relating to venue relative to business corporations, is amended by revising Code Section
13 14-2-510, relating to venue, as follows:
